quran[137]{c,v,t}:
  58,1,"Indeed, God has heard the argument of the woman who pleaded with you ňĻO Prophetňļ concerning her husband, and appealed to God. God has heard your exchange.¬†Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  58,2,"Those of you who ňĻsinfullyňļ divorce their wives by comparing them to their mothers ňĻshould know thatňļ their wives are in no way their mothers. None can be their mothers except those who gave birth to them. What they say is certainly detestable and false. Yet God is truly Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  58,3,"Those who divorce their wives in this manner, then ňĻwish toňļ retract what they said, must free a slave before they touch each other. This ňĻpenaltyňļ is meant to deter you. And God is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,4,"But if the husband cannot afford this, let him then fast two consecutive months before the couple touch each other. But if he is unable ňĻto fastňļ, then let him feed sixty poor people. This is to re-affirm your faith in God and His Messenger. These are the limits set by God. And the disbelievers will suffer a painful punishment"
  58,5,"Indeed, those who defy God and His Messenger will be debased, just like those before them. We have certainly sent down clear revelations. And the disbelievers will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  58,6,"On the Day God resurrects them all together, He will then inform them of what they have done. God has kept account of it all, while they have forgotten it. For God is a Witness over all things"
  58,7,"Do you not see that God knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? If three converse privately, He is their fourth. If five, He is their sixth. Whether fewer or more, He is with them¬†wherever they may be. Then, on the Day of Judgment, He will inform them of what they have done. Surely God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  58,8,"Have you not seen those who were forbidden from secret talks, yet they ňĻalwaysňļ return to what they were forbidden from, conspiring in sin, aggression, and disobedience to the Messenger? And when they come to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they greet you not as God greets you,¬†and say to one another, ‚ÄúWhy does God not punish us for what we say?‚ÄĚ Hell is enough for them‚ÄĒthey will burn in it. And what an evil destination"
  58,9,"O believers! When you converse privately, let it not be for sin, aggression, or disobedience to the Messenger, but let it be for goodness and righteousness. And fear God, to Whom you will ňĻallňļ be gathered"
  58,10,Secret talks are only inspired by Satan to grieve the believers. Yet he cannot harm them whatsoever except by God‚Äôs Will. So in God let the believers put their trust
  58,11,"O believers! When you are told to make room in gatherings, then do so. God will make room for you ňĻin His graceňļ. And if you are told to rise, then do so. God will elevate those of you who are faithful, and ňĻraiseňļ those gifted with knowledge in rank. And God is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,12,"O believers! When you consult the Messenger privately, give something in charity before your consultation. That is better and purer for you. But if you lack the means, then God is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  58,13,"Are you afraid of spending in charity before your private consultations ňĻwith himňļ? Since you are unable to do so, and God has turned to you in mercy, then ňĻcontinue toňļ establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey God and His Messenger. And God is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,14,Have you not seen those ňĻhypocritesňļ who ally themselves with a people with whom God is displeased? They are neither with you nor with them. And they swear to lies knowingly
  58,15,God has prepared for them a severe punishment. Evil indeed is what they do
  58,16,"They have made their ňĻfalseňļ oaths as a shield, hindering ňĻothersňļ from the cause of God. So they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  58,17,Neither their wealth nor children will be of any help to them against God whatsoever. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  58,18,"On the Day God resurrects them all, they will ňĻfalselyňļ swear to Him as they swear to you, thinking they have something to stand on. Indeed, it is they who are the ňĻtotalňļ liars"
  58,19,"Satan has taken hold of them, causing them to forget the remembrance of God. They are the party of Satan. Surely Satan‚Äôs party is bound to lose"
  58,20,"ňĻAs forňļ those who defy God and His Messenger, they will definitely be among the most debased"
  58,21,"God has decreed, ‚ÄúI and My messengers will certainly prevail.‚ÄĚ Surely God is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  58,22,"You will never find a people who ňĻtrulyňļ believe in God and the Last Day loyal to those who defy God and His Messenger, even if they were their parents, children, siblings, or extended family. For those ňĻbelieversňļ, God has instilled faith in their hearts and strengthened them with a spirit from Him.¬†He will admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. God is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. They are the party of God. Indeed, God‚Äôs party is bound to succeed"
  59,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies God. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  59,2,"He is the One Who expelled the disbelievers of the People of the Book from their homes for ňĻtheirňļ first banishment ňĻeverňļ. You never thought they would go. And they thought their strongholds would put them out of God‚Äôs reach. But ňĻthe decree ofňļ God came upon them from where they never expected. And He cast horror into their hearts so they destroyed their houses with their own hands and the hands of the believers.¬†So take a lesson ňĻfrom thisňļ, O people of insight"
  59,3,"Had God not decreed exile for them, He would have certainly punished them in this world. And in the Hereafter they will suffer the punishment of the Fire"
  59,4,"This is because they defied God and His Messenger. And whoever defies God, then God is truly severe in punishment"
  59,5,"Whatever palm trees you ňĻbelieversňļ cut down or left standing intact, it was ňĻallňļ by God‚Äôs Will, so that He might disgrace the rebellious"
  59,6,As for the gains God has turned over to His Messenger from them‚ÄĒyou did not ňĻevenňļ spur on any horse or camel for such gains. But God gives authority to His messengers over whoever He wills. For God is Most Capable of everything
  59,7,"As for gains granted by God to His Messenger from the people of ňĻotherňļ lands, they are for God and the Messenger, his close relatives, orphans, the poor, and ňĻneedyňļ travellers so that wealth may not merely circulate among your rich. Whatever the Messenger gives you, take it. And whatever he forbids you from, leave it. And fear God. Surely God is severe in punishment"
  59,8,"ňĻSome of the gains will beňļ for poor emigrants who were driven out of their homes and wealth, seeking God‚Äôs bounty and pleasure, and standing up for God and His Messenger. They are the ones true in faith"
  59,9,"As for those who had settled in the city and ňĻembracedňļ the faith before ňĻthe arrival ofňļ the emigrants, they love whoever immigrates to them, never having a desire in their hearts for whatever ňĻof the gainsňļ is given to the emigrants. They give ňĻthe emigrantsňļ preference over themselves even though they may be in need. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ successful"
  59,10,"And those who come after them will pray, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Forgive us and our fellow believers who preceded us in faith, and do not allow bitterness into our hearts towards those who believe. Our Lord! Indeed, You are Ever Gracious, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  59,11,"Have you ňĻO Prophetňļ not seen the hypocrites who say to their fellow disbelievers from the People of the Book,¬†‚ÄúIf you are expelled, we will certainly leave with you, and We will never obey anyone against you. And if you are fought against, we will surely help you.‚ÄĚ? But God bears witness that they are truly liars"
  59,12,"Indeed, if they are expelled, the hypocrites will never leave with them. And if they are fought against, the hypocrites will never help them. And even if the hypocrites did so, they would certainly flee, then the disbelievers would be left with no help"
  59,13,"Indeed, there is more fear in their hearts for you ňĻbelieversňļ than for God. That is because they are a people who do not comprehend"
  59,14,"Even united, they would not ňĻdareňļ fight against you except ňĻfromňļ within fortified strongholds or from behind walls. Their malice for each other is intense: you think they are united, yet their hearts are divided. That is because they are a people with no ňĻrealňļ understanding"
  59,15,"They are ňĻboth justňļ like those who recently went down before them:¬†they tasted the evil consequences of their doings. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  59,16,"ňĻThey areňļ like Satan when he lures someone to disbelieve. Then after they have done so, he will say ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ, ‚ÄúI have absolutely nothing to do with you. I truly fear God‚ÄĒthe Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  59,17,"So they will both end up in the Fire, staying there forever. That is the reward of the wrongdoers"
  59,18,"O believers! Be mindful of God and let every soul look to what ňĻdeedsňļ it has sent forth for tomorrow.¬†And fear God, ňĻforňļ certainly God is All-Aware of what you do"
  59,19,"And do not be like those who forgot God, so He made them forget themselves. It is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ rebellious"
  59,20,The residents of the Fire cannot be equal to the residents of Paradise. ňĻOnlyňļ the residents of Paradise will be successful
  59,21,"Had We sent down this Quran upon a mountain, you would have certainly seen it humbled and torn apart in awe of God. We set forth such comparisons for people, ňĻsoňļ perhaps they may reflect"
  59,22,"He is God‚ÄĒthere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him: Knower of the seen and unseen. He is the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  59,23,"He is God‚ÄĒthere is no god except Him: the King, the Most Holy, the All-Perfect, the Source of Serenity, the Watcher ňĻof allňļ, the Almighty, the Supreme in Might,¬†the Majestic. Glorified is God far above what they associate with Him ňĻin worshipňļ"
  59,24,"He is God: the Creator, the Inventor, the Shaper. He ňĻaloneňļ has the Most Beautiful Names. Whatever is in the heavens and the earth ňĻconstantlyňļ glorifies Him. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  60,1,"O believers! Do not take My enemies and yours as trusted allies, showing them affection even though they deny what has come to you of the truth. They drove the Messenger and yourselves out ňĻof Meccaňļ, simply for your belief in God, your Lord. If you ňĻtrulyňļ emigrated¬†to struggle in My cause and seek My pleasure, ňĻthen do not take them as allies,ňļ disclosing secrets ňĻof the believersňļ to the pagans out of affection for them, when I know best whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal. And whoever of you does this has truly strayed from the Right Way"
  60,2,"If they gain the upper hand over you, they would be your ňĻopenňļ enemies, unleashing their hands and tongues to harm you, and wishing that you would abandon faith"
  60,3,Neither your relatives nor children will benefit you on Judgment Day‚ÄĒHe will decide between you ňĻallňļ. For God is All-Seeing of what you do
  60,4,"You already have an excellent example in Abraham and those with him, when they said to their people, ‚ÄúWe totally dissociate ourselves from you and ňĻshunňļ whatever ňĻidolsňļ you worship besides God. We reject you. The enmity and hatred that has arisen between us and you will last until you believe in God alone.‚ÄĚ The only exception is when Abraham said to his father, ‚ÄúI will seek forgiveness for you,ňĻ‚ÄĚ adding, ‚Äúbutňļ I cannot protect you from God at all.‚ÄĚ ňĻThe believers prayed,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! In You we trust. And to You we ňĻalwaysňļ turn. And to You is the final return"
  60,5,"Our Lord! Do not subject us to the persecution of the disbelievers. Forgive us, our Lord! You ňĻaloneňļ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  60,6,"You certainly have an excellent example in them for whoever has hope in God and the Last Day. But whoever turns away, then surely God ňĻaloneňļ is the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  60,7,"ňĻIn time,ňļ God may bring about goodwill between you and those of them you ňĻnowňļ hold as enemies. For God is Most Capable. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,God does not forbid you from dealing kindly and fairly with those who have neither fought nor driven you out of your homes. Surely God loves those who are fair
  60,9,"God only forbids you from befriending those who have fought you for ňĻyourňļ faith, driven you out of your homes, or supported ňĻothersňļ in doing so. And whoever takes them as friends, then it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O believers! When the believing women come to you as emigrants,¬†test their intentions‚ÄĒtheir faith¬†is best known to God‚ÄĒand if you find them to be believers, then do not send them back to the disbelievers. These ňĻwomenňļ are not lawful ňĻwivesňļ for the disbelievers, nor are the disbelievers lawful ňĻhusbandsňļ for them. ňĻButňļ repay the disbelievers whatever ňĻdowriesňļ they had paid. And there is no blame on you if you marry these ňĻwomenňļ as long as you pay them their dowries. And do not hold on to marriage with polytheistic women.¬†ňĻButňļ demand ňĻrepayment ofňļ whatever ňĻdowriesňļ you had paid, and let the disbelievers do the same. That is the judgment of God‚ÄĒHe judges between you. And God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"And if any of your wives desert you to the disbelievers, and later you take spoils from them, then pay those whose wives have gone, the equivalent of whatever ňĻdowryňļ they had paid. And be mindful of God, in Whom you believe"
  60,12,"O Prophet! When the believing women come to you, pledging to you that they will neither associate anything with God ňĻin worshipňļ, nor steal, nor fornicate, nor kill their children, nor falsely attribute ňĻillegitimateňļ children to their husbands,¬†nor disobey you in what is right, then accept their pledge, and ask God to forgive them. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,13,"O believers! Do not ally yourselves with a people God is displeased with. They already have no hope for the Hereafter, just like the disbelievers lying in ňĻtheirňļ graves"
  61,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies God. For He ňĻaloneňļ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  61,2,O believers! Why do you say what you do not do
  61,3,How despicable it is in the sight of God that you say what you do not do
  61,4,Surely God loves those who fight in His cause in ňĻsolidňļ ranks as if they were one concrete structure
  61,5,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when Moses said to his people, ‚ÄúO my people! Why do you hurt me when you already know I am God‚Äôs messenger to you?‚ÄĚ So when they ňĻpersistentlyňļ deviated, God caused their hearts to deviate. For God does not guide the rebellious people"
  61,6,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Jesus, son of Mary, said, ‚ÄúO children of Israel! I am truly God‚Äôs messenger to you, confirming the Torah which came before me, and giving good news of a messenger after me whose name will be AŠł•mad.‚ÄĚ¬†Yet when the Prophet came to them with clear proofs, they said, ‚ÄúThis is pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  61,7,Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies about God when invited to submit ňĻto Himňļ?¬†For God does not guide the wrongdoing people
  61,8,"They wish to extinguish God‚Äôs light with their mouths, but God will ňĻcertainlyňļ perfect His light, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  61,9,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ňĻtrueňļ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others, even to the dismay of the polytheists"
  61,10,O believers! Shall I guide you to an exchange that will save you from a painful punishment
  61,11,"ňĻIt is toňļ have faith in God and His Messenger, and strive in the cause of God with your wealth and your lives. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  61,12,"He will forgive your sins, and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow, and ňĻhouse you inňļ splendid homes in the Gardens of Eternity. That is the ultimate triumph"
  61,13,"ňĻHe will also give youňļ another favour that you long for: help from God and an imminent victory. ňĻSoňļ give good news ňĻO Prophetňļ to the believers"
  61,14,"O believers! Stand up for God, as Jesus, son of Mary, asked the disciples, ‚ÄúWho will stand up with me for God?‚ÄĚ The disciples replied, ‚ÄúWe will stand up for God.‚ÄĚ Then a group from the Children of Israel believed while another disbelieved. We then supported the believers against their enemies, so they prevailed"
  62,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth ňĻconstantlyňļ glorifies God‚ÄĒthe King, the Most Holy, the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  62,2,"He is the One Who raised for the illiterate ňĻpeopleňļ a messenger from among themselves‚ÄĒreciting to them His revelations, purifying them, and teaching them the Book and wisdom, for indeed they had previously been clearly astray‚ÄĒ"
  62,3,"along with others of them who have not yet joined them ňĻin faithňļ. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  62,4,This is the favour of God. He grants it to whoever He wills. And God is the Lord of infinite bounty
  62,5,"The example of those who were entrusted with ňĻobservingňļ the Torah but failed to do so, is that of a donkey carrying books.¬†How evil is the example of those who reject God‚Äôs signs! For God does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  62,6,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO Jews! If you claim to be God‚Äôs chosen ňĻpeopleňļ out of all humanity, then wish for death, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  62,7,But they will never wish for that because of what their hands have done.¬†And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the wrongdoers
  62,8,"Say, ‚ÄúThe death you are running away from will inevitably come to you. Then you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, and He will inform you of what you used to do.‚ÄĚ"
  62,9,"O believers! When the call to prayer is made on Friday, then proceed ňĻdiligentlyňļ to the remembrance of God and leave off ňĻyourňļ business. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  62,10,"Once the prayer is over, disperse throughout the land and seek the bounty of God. And remember God often so you may be successful"
  62,11,"When they saw the fanfare along with the caravan, they ňĻalmost allňļ flocked to it, leaving you ňĻO Prophetňļ standing ňĻon the pulpitňļ. Say, ‚ÄúWhat is with God is far better than amusement and merchandise. And God is the Best Provider.‚ÄĚ"
  63,1,"When the hypocrites come to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they say, ‚ÄúWe bear witness that you are certainly the Messenger of God‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒand surely God knows that you are His Messenger‚ÄĒbut God bears witness that the hypocrites are truly liars"
  63,2,"They have made their ňĻfalseňļ oaths as a shield, hindering ňĻothersňļ from the Way of God. Evil indeed is what they do"
  63,3,"This is because they believed and then abandoned faith. Therefore, their hearts have been sealed, so they do not comprehend"
  63,4,"When you see them, their appearance impresses you. And when they speak, you listen to their ňĻimpressiveňļ speech. But they are ňĻjustňļ like ňĻworthlessňļ planks of wood leaned ňĻagainst a wallňļ. They think every cry is against them. They are the enemy, so beware of them. May God condemn them! How can they be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  63,5,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúCome! The Messenger of God will pray for you to be forgiven,‚ÄĚ they turn their heads ňĻin disgustňļ, and you see them ňĻO Prophetňļ turn away in arrogance"
  63,6,"It is the same whether you pray for their forgiveness or not, God will not forgive them. Surely God does not guide the rebellious people"
  63,7,"They are the ones who say ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúDo not spend ňĻanythingňļ on those ňĻemigrantsňļ with the Messenger of God so that they will break away ňĻfrom himňļ.‚ÄĚ But to God ňĻaloneňļ belong the treasuries of the heavens and the earth, yet the hypocrites do not comprehend"
  63,8,"They say, ‚ÄúIf we return to Medina, the honourable will definitely expel the inferior.‚ÄĚ But all honour and power belongs to God, His Messenger, and the believers, yet the hypocrites do not know"
  63,9,"O believers! Do not let your wealth or your children divert you from the remembrance of God. For whoever does so, it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ losers"
  63,10,"And donate from what We have provided for you before death comes to one of you, and you cry, ‚ÄúMy Lord! If only You delayed me for a short while, I would give in charity and be one of the righteous.‚ÄĚ"
  63,11,But God never delays a soul when its appointed time comes. And God is All-Aware of what you do
  64,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth ňĻconstantlyňļ glorifies God. The kingdom is His, and all praise is for Him. For He is Most Capable of everything"
  64,2,"He is the One Who created you, yet some of you are disbelievers while some are believers. And God is All-Seeing of what you do"
  64,3,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He shaped you ňĻin the wombňļ, perfecting your form. And to Him is the final return"
  64,4,He knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal. For God knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart
  64,5,"Have the stories of those who disbelieved before not reached you ňĻpagansňļ? They tasted the evil consequences of their doings, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  64,6,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they said ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúHow can humans be our guides?‚ÄĚ So they persisted in disbelief and turned away. And God was not in need ňĻof their faithňļ. For God is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  64,7,"The disbelievers claim they will not be resurrected. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYes, by my Lord, you will surely be resurrected, then you will certainly be informed of what you have done. And that is easy for God.‚ÄĚ"
  64,8,So believe in God and His Messenger and in the Light¬†We have revealed. And God is All-Aware of what you do
  64,9,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day He will gather you ňĻallňļ for the Day of Gathering‚ÄĒthat will be the Day of mutual loss and gain. So whoever believes in God and does good, He will absolve them of their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  64,10,"As for those who disbelieve and reject Our revelations, they will be the residents of the Fire, staying there forever. What an evil destination"
  64,11,"No calamity befalls ňĻanyoneňļ except by God‚Äôs Will. And whoever has faith in God, He will ňĻrightlyňļ guide their hearts ňĻthrough adversityňļ. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  64,12,"Obey God and obey the Messenger! But if you turn away, then Our Messenger‚Äôs duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly"
  64,13,God‚ÄĒthere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. So in God let the believers put their trust
  64,14,"O believers! Indeed, some of your spouses and children are enemies to you,¬†so beware of them. But if you pardon, overlook, and forgive ňĻtheir faultsňļ, then God is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  64,15,"Your wealth and children are only a test, but God ňĻaloneňļ has a great reward"
  64,16,"So be mindful of God to the best of your ability, hear and obey, and spend in charity‚ÄĒthat will be best for you. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ successful"
  64,17,"If you lend to God a good loan, He will multiply it for you and forgive you. For God is Most Appreciative, Most Forbearing"
  64,18,"ňĻHe is theňļ Knower of the seen and unseen‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  65,1,"O Prophet! ňĻInstruct the believers:ňļ When you ňĻintend toňļ divorce women, then divorce them with concern for their waiting period,¬†and count it accurately. And¬†fear God, your Lord. Do not force them out of their homes, nor should they leave‚ÄĒunless they commit a blatant misconduct. These are the limits set by God. And whoever transgresses God‚Äôs limits has truly wronged his own soul. You never know, perhaps God will bring about a change ňĻof heartňļ later"
  65,2,"Then when they have ňĻalmostňļ reached the end of their waiting period, either retain them honourably or separate from them honourably.¬†And call two of your reliable men to witness ňĻeither wayňļ‚ÄĒand ňĻlet the witnessesňļ bear true testimony for ňĻthe sake ofňļ God. This is enjoined on whoever has faith in God and the Last Day. And whoever is mindful of God, He will make a way out for them"
  65,3,"and provide for them from sources they could never imagine. And whoever puts their trust in God, then He ňĻaloneňļ is sufficient for them. Certainly God achieves His Will. God has already set a destiny for everything"
  65,4,"As for your women past the age of menstruation, in case you do not know, their waiting period is three months, and those who have not menstruated as well. As for those who are pregnant, their waiting period ends with delivery.¬†And whoever is mindful of God, He will make their matters easy for them"
  65,5,"This is the commandment of God, which He has revealed to you. And whoever is mindful of God, He will absolve them of their sins and reward them immensely"
  65,6,"Let them live where you live ňĻduring their waiting periodňļ, according to your means. And do not harass them to make their stay unbearable. If they are pregnant, then maintain them until they deliver. And if they nurse your child,¬†compensate them, and consult together courteously. But if you fail to reach an agreement, then another woman will nurse ňĻthe childňļ for the father"
  65,7,"Let the man of wealth provide according to his means. As for the one with limited resources, let him provide according to whatever God has given him. God does not require of any soul beyond what He has given it. After hardship, God will bring about ease"
  65,8,"ňĻImagineňļ how many societies rebelled against the commandments of their Lord and His messengers, so We called each ňĻsocietyňļ to a severe account and subjected them to a horrible punishment"
  65,9,"So they tasted the evil consequences of their doings, and the outcome of their doings was ňĻtotalňļ loss"
  65,10,"God has ňĻalsoňļ prepared for them a severe punishment. So fear God, O people of reason and faith. God has indeed revealed to you a Reminder"
  65,11,"ňĻand sentňļ a messenger reciting to you God‚Äôs revelations, making things clear so that He may bring those who believe and do good out of darkness and into light. And whoever believes in God and does good will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. God will have indeed granted them an excellent provision"
  65,12,"God is the One Who created seven heavens ňĻin layersňļ, and likewise for the earth. The ňĻdivineňļ command descends between them so you may know that God is Most Capable of everything and that God certainly encompasses all things in ňĻHisňļ knowledge"
  66,1,"O Prophet! Why do you prohibit ňĻyourselfňļ from what God has made lawful to you, seeking to please your wives? And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
