  66,4,"ňĻIt will be betterňļ if you ňĻwivesňļ both turn to God in repentance, for your hearts have certainly faltered. But if you ňĻcontinue toňļ collaborate against him, then ňĻknow thatňļ God Himself is his Guardian. And Gabriel, the righteous believers, and the angels are ňĻallňļ his supporters as well"
  66,5,"Perhaps, if he were to divorce you ňĻallňļ, his Lord would replace you with better wives who are submissive ňĻto Godňļ, faithful ňĻto Himňļ, devout, repentant, dedicated to worship and fasting‚ÄĒpreviously married or virgins"
  66,6,"O believers! Protect yourselves and your families from a Fire whose fuel is people and stones, overseen by formidable and severe angels, who never disobey whatever God orders‚ÄĒalways doing as commanded"
  66,7,"ňĻThe deniers will then be told,ňļ ‚ÄúO disbelievers! Make no excuses this Day! You are only rewarded for what you used to do.‚ÄĚ"
  66,8,"O believers! Turn to God in sincere repentance, so your Lord may absolve you of your sins and admit you into Gardens, under which rivers flow, on the Day God will not disgrace the Prophet or the believers with him. Their light will shine ahead of them and on their right. They will say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Perfect our light for us, and forgive us. ňĻForňļ You are truly Most Capable of everything.‚ÄĚ"
  66,9,"O Prophet! Struggle against the disbelievers and the hypocrites, and be firm with them. Hell will be their home. What an evil destination"
  66,10,"God sets forth an example for the disbelievers: the wife of Noah and the wife of Lot. Each was married to one of Our righteous servants, yet betrayed them.¬†So their husbands were of no benefit to them against God whatsoever. Both were told, ‚ÄúEnter the Fire, along with the others!‚ÄĚ"
  66,11,"And God sets forth an example for the believers: the wife of Pharaoh, who prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Build me a house in Paradise near You, deliver me from Pharaoh and his ňĻevilňļ doing, and save me from the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
